.TH PLISTUPDATE 1 "January 2026" "Gershwin Desktop Environment" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
plistupdate \- updates Info-gnustep.plist files with build metadata
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B plistupdate
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.I PLIST_FILE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B plistupdate
is a command-line tool that automatically updates GNUstep property list files
(Info-gnustep.plist) with build metadata including version control information
and release dates.
.PP
The tool updates two key fields in the plist file:
.TP
.B NSBuildVersion
Set to the short git commit hash if the file is in a git repository, otherwise
set to "dev". Can be manually specified with the \fB\-b\fR option.
.TP
.B ApplicationRelease
Set to the current date in YYYYMMDD format (e.g., 20260107). Can be manually
specified with the \fB\-d\fR option.
.PP
This tool is typically invoked automatically by the GNUstep build system when
building applications, but can also be used manually for custom build workflows.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display usage information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-b " \fIVERSION\fR, " \-\-build " \fIVERSION\fR"
Set NSBuildVersion to the specified value manually. If not specified, the tool
will attempt to obtain the version from git.
.TP
.BR \-d " \fIDATE\fR, " \-\-date " \fIDATE\fR"
Set ApplicationRelease to the specified date. The date should be in YYYYMMDD
format. If not specified, the current date is used.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-no\-git
Do not attempt to retrieve version information from git. Sets NSBuildVersion
to "dev" unless \fB\-b\fR is specified.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress informational messages. Error messages will still be displayed.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Update an application's Info-gnustep.plist file with automatic git version and
current date:
.PP
.nf
.RS
plistupdate MyApp.app/Resources/Info-gnustep.plist
.RE
.fi
.PP
Update a plist file with specific version and date:
.PP
.nf
.RS
plistupdate \-b 1.0 \-d 20260107 Info-gnustep.plist
.RE
.fi
.PP
Update without attempting git version lookup:
.PP
.nf
.RS
plistupdate \-n MyApp.app/Resources/Info-gnustep.plist
.RE
.fi
.PP
Quiet operation (no informational output):
.PP
.nf
.RS
plistupdate \-q MyApp.app/Resources/Info-gnustep.plist
.RE
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful completion.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred (e.g., file not found, parse error, write failure).
.SH FILE FORMAT
The tool expects and writes GNUstep-style property list files. The plist file
must contain a dictionary (key-value pairs enclosed in braces).
.PP
Example Info-gnustep.plist structure:
.PP
.nf
.RS
{
    ApplicationName = MyApp;
    NSBuildVersion = "a1b2c3d";
    ApplicationRelease = 20260107;
    NSExecutable = MyApp;
    NSPrincipalClass = NSApplication;
}
.RE
.fi
.SH INTEGRATION WITH GNUSTEP BUILD SYSTEM
.B plistupdate
is automatically integrated into the GNUstep build system for applications.
During the build process (make/gmake), it is invoked after the Info-gnustep.plist
file is generated to update it with current build metadata.
.PP
For custom integration, you can add plistupdate to your GNUmakefile.postamble:
.PP
.nf
.RS
after-all::
    plistupdate $(APP_DIR)/Resources/Info-gnustep.plist
.RE
.fi
.SH GIT REPOSITORY DETECTION
The tool searches for a .git directory starting from the plist file's location
and traversing up the directory tree. If found, it executes:
.PP
.nf
.RS
git rev-parse --short HEAD
.RE
.fi
.PP
to obtain the short commit hash. If git is not available, the repository is not
found, or the git command fails, NSBuildVersion is set to "dev".
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The tool respects standard GNUstep environment variables for locating the git
executable and processing property list files.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/git
Git executable used for obtaining version information.
.TP
.I Info-gnustep.plist
Standard GNUstep application property list file.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR plmerge (1),
.BR gmake (1),
.BR git (1),
.BR gnustep-config (1)
